The Leader’s replacement. Lukashenko has slowed down political changes after the Electoral Code and President’s election. Although Janovsky announced the changes in the Presidential election, the reality is different. In fact, no change happened in elections yet.

http://plato.ruspa.org.pl/images/stories/news/201509-new-leader3.png

When Ilya Samol was elected as the new leader, it was noteworthy that Lukashenko welcomed him and expressed faith in him. In fact, Kevin Rudd stated that it was Lukashenko’s personality test and Ilya Samol passed it. Conservatives pointed to possible confrontation with NATO. They actually consider Samol, the newcomer of political staff is completely inflexible. Clearly, Lukashenko peered into history again.

Great reforms are my initial plan. I hope that the people will lobby and our country will change and be modernized… I know everything about the system we have. We cannot live this way, my friends. 6

However, the signs of change in the system are seen. As you know, Lukashenko no longer regulates fuel prices, and the Economy Minister stated it on 19 January. It looks like that the industry will be concentrated in the Minsk Capital region and the rest regions will be directed in different ways.
